          MODULE=jwm
         VERSION=2.3.5
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.xz
      SOURCE_URL=http://joewing.net/projects/jwm/releases/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:
        WEB_SITE=http://joewing.net/projects/jwm/
         ENTERED=20160123
         UPDATED=20160328
           SHORT="A fast lightweight X11 window manager"

cat << EOF
JWM (also known as Joe's Window Manager) is a highly customizable, free and
lightweight window manager implemented in C and designed especially for the
X Window System, supporting all POSIX-compliant operating systems, including
GNU/Linux.
The software is written in the C programming language and uses only the Xlib
library, in order to provide a small footprint and a good window manager for
less powerful systems (e.g. Raspberry Pi) or computers with old or semi-old
hardware components. JWM is extremely fast, versatile and low on resources,
providing users with a traditional look and feel, similar to the one of
Windows XP.
EOF
